  "prompt": "Why are dildos called dildos?",
  "response": "The origin of the term \"dildo\" is somewhat unclear, but there are several possible explanations. One theory traces it back to the Italian word \"diletto,\" meaning \"delight.\" Another suggests it comes from the archaic English word \"dildynge,\" which meant \"to be defiant or wanton.\"\n\nThe word \"dildo\" first appeared in English literature in the late 17th century, and over time, it came to specifically refer to a phallic-shaped object used for sexual pleasure. It's likely that the name evolved as part of vernacular language surrounding intimacy and sex toys.\n\nWhile the exact source is unknown, the name has become widely recognized and standardized in reference to these types of products.",
